File: Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula. JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula is calling for extra caution on the roads. He says he's is saddened by the spate of fatal crashes this long weekend. READ: Use public transport first, mayor tells Mboweni Six people were burnt beyond recognition after two cars collided head-on before one of them burst into flames in Dingamazi village in Giyani, Limpopo. Two people were also killed in the same province, and at least 80 others were injured in a collision involving a bus, bakkie and an SUV. In Mpumalanga, a crash claimed the lives of six people. Mbalula's also called on law enforcement officials to continue ensuring adherence to road rules.